WEBVTT

1
00:00:04,004 --> 00:00:05,429
HENRY:
<i>I’ll be gone in a week.</i>

2
00:00:05,464 --> 00:00:06,680
Your mother’ll miss you.

3
00:00:06,715 --> 00:00:08,599
‐ Taking her with me, Alan.
‐ What?

4
00:00:08,634 --> 00:00:10,142
<i>She barely knows
what year it is.</i>

5
00:00:10,177 --> 00:00:12,019
Take off your shoes.
You know your father

6
00:00:12,054 --> 00:00:13,979
won’t abide
any click‐clacks in the house.

7
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,564
ALAN:
<i>They call it sundownin’.</i>

8
00:00:15,599 --> 00:00:17,434
<i>Nights are hard for your mom.</i>

9
00:00:23,524 --> 00:00:24,823
ALAN:
<i>Warden Lacy,</i>

10
00:00:24,858 --> 00:00:28,202
he told me the Devil was a boy,

11
00:00:28,237 --> 00:00:30,412
and old Dale said he caught him.

12
00:00:30,447 --> 00:00:33,123
<i>Had locked the Devil in a box.</i>

13
00:00:33,158 --> 00:00:36,084
LACY: <i>To put an end to all
the horrors we’ve seen,</i>

14
00:00:36,119 --> 00:00:38,003
<i>that’s what God told me.</i>

15
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:39,630
How long ago was this?

16
00:00:39,665 --> 00:00:41,423
ALAN: <i>Don’t let
that fuckin’ kid out.</i>

17
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:43,175
Is it time to call Pruitt?

18
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:46,261
Hey! I can be your lawyer
if you want me to be.

19
00:00:46,296 --> 00:00:48,472
‐ But you have to say it.
‐ ZALEWSKI: <i>We’re both</i>

20
00:00:48,507 --> 00:00:49,667
gettin’ out of this shithole.

21
00:00:51,593 --> 00:00:53,387
( door unlocking )

22
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:58,475
( alarms ringing )

23
00:01:00,936 --> 00:01:02,437
‐ Sit the fuck‐‐ ‐ ( gunshot )

24
00:01:03,647 --> 00:01:04,648
( explosion )

25
00:01:11,196 --> 00:01:12,162
WOMAN:
<i>I’m gonna read you</i>

26
00:01:12,197 --> 00:01:13,726
<i>a list of five words.</i>

27
00:01:14,366 --> 00:01:16,833
I’m gonna ask you to repeat them
in any order.

28
00:01:16,868 --> 00:01:19,703
Once now, and then again
in a few minutes.

29
00:01:20,330 --> 00:01:21,415
You ready?

30
00:01:23,417 --> 00:01:27,219
Boat, family, church,

31
00:01:27,753 --> 00:01:30,467
dog, white.

32
00:01:30,924 --> 00:01:33,265
Boat, white, church...

33
00:01:34,511 --> 00:01:35,695
dog...

34
00:01:36,692 --> 00:01:38,068
family.

35
00:01:39,873 --> 00:01:42,292
( machine whirring )

36
00:01:47,274 --> 00:01:48,775
( beeping )

37
00:01:50,986 --> 00:01:54,656
( machine clacking, vibrating )

38
00:02:15,469 --> 00:02:16,476
( door opens )

39
00:02:16,628 --> 00:02:18,359
WOMAN: You okay?

40
00:02:18,430 --> 00:02:19,431
Yeah.

41
00:02:26,563 --> 00:02:29,164
I’m not supposed
to tell you this, but...

42
00:02:29,775 --> 00:02:32,171
your scan looks clear. To me.

43
00:02:33,070 --> 00:02:34,953
Doctor Green will walk through
your results.

44
00:02:34,988 --> 00:02:37,140
So, what is it?

45
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:40,667
Do you listen to loud music
in your earbuds?

46
00:02:40,702 --> 00:02:42,625
It could just be tinnitus.

47
00:02:43,372 --> 00:02:45,797
‐ Do you hear it right now?
‐ Comes and goes.

48
00:02:45,832 --> 00:02:48,210
Used to bother me
when I was a teenager.

49
00:02:49,711 --> 00:02:51,178
Where you from?

50
00:02:51,213 --> 00:02:52,804
I know you’re not a Texan.

51
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:54,681
New Yorker.

52
00:02:54,949 --> 00:02:56,332
Maine.

53
00:02:56,368 --> 00:02:58,168
That’s nice.

54
00:02:58,234 --> 00:02:59,895
Flat houses, snow on Christmas.

55
00:02:59,930 --> 00:03:01,313
( chuckles )

56
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:02,522
Yeah.

57
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:03,774
Not exactly.

58
00:03:04,184 --> 00:03:05,518
You get back there much?

59
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:07,853
No.

60
00:03:10,816 --> 00:03:12,532
I guess everyone thinks
they grew up

61
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:13,847
in the worst place
on earth, huh?

62
00:03:18,824 --> 00:03:20,540
( sirens wail )

63
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:21,917
MAN: <i>Five days
after the massacre,</i>

64
00:03:21,952 --> 00:03:24,586
<i>we still have so few answers.</i>

65
00:03:24,621 --> 00:03:26,880
<i>Why did the much‐liked
corrections officer</i>

66
00:03:26,915 --> 00:03:28,507
<i>unleash on his fellow guards?</i>

67
00:03:28,542 --> 00:03:30,217
<i>Along with the shocking...</i>
( voice fades )

68
00:03:30,252 --> 00:03:31,718
WOMAN: <i>...privatizing
of the prison,</i>

69
00:03:31,753 --> 00:03:33,720
<i>along with the suicide
of its beloved warden,</i>

70
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:36,264
<i>the tragedies at Shawshank
keep piling up.</i>

71
00:03:36,299 --> 00:03:37,808
MAN 2:
<i>In other news, the wildfires</i>

72
00:03:37,843 --> 00:03:40,435
<i>continue to spread across
Black Mountain,</i>

73
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:42,479
<i>engulfing as many as 200 acres.</i>

74
00:03:42,514 --> 00:03:44,940
<i>Firefighting teams from across
the state are pitching in,</i>

75
00:03:44,975 --> 00:03:48,110
<i>but the residents of dozens
of houses between Castle View</i>

76
00:03:48,145 --> 00:03:51,445
<i>and Castle Lake
have already been evacuated.</i>

77
00:03:52,190 --> 00:03:54,067
( sirens wail )

78
00:03:58,113 --> 00:03:59,621
I know. I already had
a hearing scheduled.

79
00:03:59,656 --> 00:04:01,984
They pushed it
three weeks after‐‐

80
00:04:03,118 --> 00:04:04,960
That’s what I’m trying to tell‐‐
Look, look...

81
00:04:04,995 --> 00:04:06,962
I‐I left two messages
with the judge.

82
00:04:06,997 --> 00:04:09,506
I have a client who’s stuck
in Shawshank, and I‐‐

83
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:10,541
Hello?

84
00:04:11,168 --> 00:04:12,859
‐ Fuck!
‐ ( distant shouting )

85
00:04:13,941 --> 00:04:15,280
Sorry, Father.

86
00:04:16,214 --> 00:04:18,181
‐ Thanks for coming down.
‐ Yeah, sorry for the delay.

87
00:04:18,216 --> 00:04:19,641
Um...

88
00:04:19,676 --> 00:04:21,726
I spoke to the cemetery,
they said they should

89
00:04:21,761 --> 00:04:23,061
have a plot for my dad
ready by tomorrow.

90
00:04:23,096 --> 00:04:24,222
That’s not why I called.

91
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:36,943
( water dripping )

92
00:04:50,253 --> 00:04:52,812
It’s called
exploding casket syndrome.

93
00:04:53,084 --> 00:04:57,593
Uh, when there’s no oxygen
to dehydrate the... contents,

94
00:04:57,923 --> 00:05:01,984
the casket
becomes a pressure cooker.

95
00:05:02,344 --> 00:05:05,270
Wouldn’t think remains this old
would be susceptible, but,

96
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:07,856
maybe when they resealed
the casket for transport...

97
00:05:07,891 --> 00:05:10,650
‐ ( Henry grunts )
‐ Are you all right?

98
00:05:10,685 --> 00:05:12,027
( muffled explosion )

99
00:05:12,062 --> 00:05:13,522
( muffled gunshot )

100
00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:18,492
( muffled ) Of course, with
the recent trouble at Shawshank,

101
00:05:18,527 --> 00:05:22,913
there is a bit of a queue,
if you still want a service.

102
00:05:22,948 --> 00:05:25,791
MAN ( on speaker phone ):
<i>Let me understand this.</i>

103
00:05:25,826 --> 00:05:27,793
<i>You found
the Count of Monte Cristo</i>

104
00:05:27,828 --> 00:05:30,086
<i>in a septic tank.</i>

105
00:05:30,121 --> 00:05:32,172
<i>He asks for his lawyer,
lawyer shows up,</i>

106
00:05:32,207 --> 00:05:34,633
<i>you stiff‐arm the guy
to cover your ass,</i>

107
00:05:34,668 --> 00:05:38,261
<i>one of our own guards
doesn’t like this miscarriage</i>

108
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:40,639
<i>of justice, not one bit,</i>

109
00:05:40,674 --> 00:05:42,390
<i>so he does
the only logical thing</i>

110
00:05:42,425 --> 00:05:44,893
<i>and pumps two clips
into his coworkers.</i>

111
00:05:44,928 --> 00:05:48,438
<i>And voila!
Our very own Times alert.</i>

112
00:05:48,473 --> 00:05:51,900
<i>And yeah, I’d like to take
a moment of silence,</i>

113
00:05:51,935 --> 00:05:54,361
<i>mourn the dead,
be human for a change,</i>

114
00:05:54,396 --> 00:05:56,571
<i>I really would, but I can’t</i>

115
00:05:56,606 --> 00:05:59,533
<i>because I’m so busy
getting fucked in the ass</i>

116
00:05:59,568 --> 00:06:02,285
<i>by your incompetence.</i>

117
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:04,371
<i>I don’t care if you make him
vanish into thin air</i>

118
00:06:04,406 --> 00:06:07,040
<i>like Harry fuckin’ Houdini,
I don’t care if you bury him</i>

119
00:06:07,075 --> 00:06:09,751
<i>under the yard or buy him
a ticket to Mallorca‐‐</i>

120
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:12,629
<i>whatever happens in there,
however it gets handled,</i>

121
00:06:12,664 --> 00:06:16,281
<i>I knew nothing.
The board knew nothing.</i>

122
00:06:16,585 --> 00:06:19,085
<i>And if things go wrong, Theresa,</i>

123
00:06:19,838 --> 00:06:21,847
<i>there’s always room
under the bus</i>

124
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:24,140
<i>for one more rogue employee.</i>

125
00:06:24,175 --> 00:06:25,635
<i>( phone disconnects )</i>

126
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:38,446
<i>( alarm chimes )</i>

127
00:06:38,481 --> 00:06:39,823
AUTOMATED VOICE:
<i>Front door open.</i>

128
00:06:39,858 --> 00:06:41,101
ALAN:
Who the fuck’s that?

129
00:06:42,027 --> 00:06:43,660
HENRY:
New system.

130
00:06:43,734 --> 00:06:45,569
So we can keep an eye on Mom.

131
00:06:46,891 --> 00:06:48,399
Both doors are rigged.

132
00:06:49,187 --> 00:06:50,614
Had to get creative
with the cameras.

133
00:06:50,649 --> 00:06:52,574
Four upstairs and four down.

134
00:06:52,812 --> 00:06:54,963
As soon as I’m done
at Shawshank, I’m leaving.

135
00:06:55,117 --> 00:06:56,965
Meantime, we can both
keep an eye on her

136
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,335
with a smartphone app.

137
00:07:01,596 --> 00:07:05,231
Listen, until we figure out
the long‐term situation,

138
00:07:05,406 --> 00:07:06,824
I need to know she’s safe.

139
00:07:08,219 --> 00:07:09,811
Why not just put a chip in her,

140
00:07:09,846 --> 00:07:11,671
like a golden retriever?

141
00:07:12,307 --> 00:07:14,100
( phone chimes )

142
00:07:16,936 --> 00:07:18,146
Hello?

143
00:07:19,606 --> 00:07:20,649
Wait, what?

144
00:07:25,028 --> 00:07:26,529
How soon?

145
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:39,549
NARRATOR: <i>Three challenges will
face you, the newly paroled,</i>

146
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:41,468
<i>as you reenter society.</i>

147
00:07:41,878 --> 00:07:43,970
<i>What do I do?
Where will I live?</i>

148
00:07:44,453 --> 00:07:47,375
<i>And, finally, who will I be?</i>

149
00:07:47,801 --> 00:07:51,645
<i>The good news is, you can be
almost anyone you want to be</i>

150
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:54,230
<i>if you adapt
to your new surroundings.</i>

151
00:07:54,413 --> 00:07:57,569
<i>You will face questions
about your time in prison.</i>

152
00:07:57,769 --> 00:08:00,070
<i>When you meet
a potential employer,</i>

153
00:08:00,105 --> 00:08:02,405
<i>a potential landlord,
or even a new friend,</i>

154
00:08:02,742 --> 00:08:06,325
<i>don’t be afraid to reframe
your narrative.</i>

155
00:08:06,587 --> 00:08:08,632
<i>The person you were
when you went in,</i>

156
00:08:09,272 --> 00:08:11,890
<i>that’s not the person
walking out today.</i>

157
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,804
<i>You can tell your own story,</i>

158
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,419
<i>be your own hero,</i>

159
00:08:16,454 --> 00:08:19,082
<i>choose the life
you want to live.</i>

160
00:08:20,542 --> 00:08:23,945
<i>I’m Lou Hadley, who are you?</i>

161
00:08:24,629 --> 00:08:25,755
( door buzzing )

162
00:08:28,758 --> 00:08:30,301
( distant siren wails )

163
00:09:00,123 --> 00:09:02,674
Look at that.

164
00:09:02,709 --> 00:09:04,044
Free man.

165
00:09:05,795 --> 00:09:08,006
( chatter, laughter )

166
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:12,892
There’s a burn
on Black Mountain.

167
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:14,310
State uses inmates
during fire season.

168
00:09:14,345 --> 00:09:15,664
Why don’t we...

169
00:09:16,774 --> 00:09:18,242
Why don’t we start from scratch?

170
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:20,978
I’m Henry.

171
00:09:27,488 --> 00:09:30,085
I’m‐‐ I’m just asking your name.

172
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:38,036
<i>( theme music playing )</i>

173
00:10:08,457 --> 00:10:11,453
"Make thee an ark of gopherwood,

174
00:10:12,799 --> 00:10:16,054
and this is the fashion
thou shalt make it of."

175
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:29,045
So I built my ark...

176
00:10:31,631 --> 00:10:34,140
and when his voice
came into my dreams

177
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:36,643
for six nights in a row,

178
00:10:36,678 --> 00:10:40,234
he told me exactly where
he would stand at the quarry.

179
00:10:41,224 --> 00:10:45,007
The reason, the stain,
the curse on our town,

180
00:10:46,146 --> 00:10:49,190
dragging evil behind you
everywhere you went.

181
00:10:52,777 --> 00:10:54,369
And when I brought you
down here,

182
00:10:54,404 --> 00:10:58,492
I was on fire
with the Holy Spirit,

183
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:02,287
righteous, and so strong.

184
00:11:04,372 --> 00:11:06,207
And‐and you looked...

185
00:11:08,710 --> 00:11:12,130
you looked so small
next to my faith.

186
00:11:19,427 --> 00:11:21,346
And now...

187
00:11:22,918 --> 00:11:24,890
...now you still look small.

188
00:11:26,853 --> 00:11:28,521
But I look old.

189
00:11:31,608 --> 00:11:33,193
I am old.

190
00:11:34,694 --> 00:11:36,289
After all these years,

191
00:11:36,487 --> 00:11:38,914
I still don’t know
what you really are

192
00:11:39,730 --> 00:11:41,899
or if I did the right thing.

193
00:12:22,325 --> 00:12:24,083
Do you remember that crazy story

194
00:12:24,118 --> 00:12:25,912
you told me
your first night in here?

195
00:12:43,754 --> 00:12:45,214
Face.

196
00:12:48,624 --> 00:12:50,584
No face.

197
00:12:52,378 --> 00:12:53,963
Face.

198
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:56,776
Face.

199
00:12:59,779 --> 00:13:02,038
WOMAN:
<i>Pure retrograde amnesia.</i>

200
00:13:02,073 --> 00:13:04,415
No sign of impairment
to the short‐term memory

201
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:06,709
or structural damage
to the brain.

202
00:13:06,744 --> 00:13:09,295
A purely emotional phenomenon.

203
00:13:09,330 --> 00:13:11,256
Now I’m going to read you
a list of five words,

204
00:13:11,291 --> 00:13:14,092
I’m going to ask you
to repeat them to me

205
00:13:14,476 --> 00:13:16,141
in any order.

206
00:13:16,372 --> 00:13:17,373
Ready?

207
00:13:18,867 --> 00:13:21,516
Face, velvet, church,

208
00:13:21,754 --> 00:13:23,172
family, red.

209
00:13:25,786 --> 00:13:28,879
Face, velvet, red,

210
00:13:29,110 --> 00:13:31,404
church, family.

211
00:13:33,361 --> 00:13:34,779
So, uh...

212
00:13:36,232 --> 00:13:37,532
how do you treat it?

213
00:13:37,567 --> 00:13:38,908
There’s no magic bullet.

214
00:13:38,943 --> 00:13:40,702
Sometimes it’s
a gradual process,

215
00:13:40,737 --> 00:13:43,705
other cases, you put someone
back in their own home

216
00:13:43,740 --> 00:13:45,415
with their own junk
and it’s just like

217
00:13:45,450 --> 00:13:46,617
flipping a light switch.

218
00:13:48,453 --> 00:13:50,086
Best medicine’s to get him home.

219
00:13:50,121 --> 00:13:52,540
Restore the context,
restore the memories.

220
00:13:57,804 --> 00:13:58,970
But don’t push it.

221
00:13:59,005 --> 00:14:00,888
These things take time.

222
00:14:00,923 --> 00:14:01,923
Oh, no, no.

223
00:14:02,625 --> 00:14:04,434
No, I’m just his lawyer.

224
00:14:04,469 --> 00:14:07,311
I brought him here so you all
could take care of him.

225
00:14:07,346 --> 00:14:09,605
Well, we’re not
an inpatient facility.

226
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,691
I could pull some strings
at Juniper Hill,

227
00:14:11,726 --> 00:14:14,193
might be able to get him
a bed by Monday.

228
00:14:14,344 --> 00:14:15,537
By Monday?

229
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:18,691
<i>What’s he supposed to do
until Monday?</i>

230
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:22,452
( whirring )

231
00:14:22,487 --> 00:14:25,329
MOLLY: So the bathroom
is back that way,

232
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:28,576
there’s no shower,
just don’t drink the water.

233
00:14:34,207 --> 00:14:36,758
HENRY: You should really
stay in here this weekend, OK?

234
00:14:36,793 --> 00:14:38,468
Nobody in town knows you’re out.

235
00:14:38,706 --> 00:14:40,666
Let’s keep it that way.

236
00:14:45,955 --> 00:14:47,498
I don’t think
this is a good idea.

237
00:14:50,223 --> 00:14:52,148
I appreciate you
trying to help, but...

238
00:14:52,183 --> 00:14:53,983
He needs a place to sleep,

239
00:14:54,205 --> 00:14:55,625
and I’ve got one.

240
00:15:15,706 --> 00:15:17,298
Look, we have no idea who he is.

241
00:15:17,817 --> 00:15:20,187
He could be
the Bangor Strangler.

242
00:15:20,354 --> 00:15:22,077
First of all, you made that up.

243
00:15:22,609 --> 00:15:24,931
Second, you’re the one
who got him out of prison.

244
00:15:24,966 --> 00:15:27,183
Yeah, because I believe
in due process.

245
00:15:27,218 --> 00:15:29,018
Doesn’t mean I want him

246
00:15:29,373 --> 00:15:30,708
bunking up with my...

247
00:15:31,708 --> 00:15:33,251
friend.

